com.esotericsoftware.kryo.io

Class UnsafeOutput

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.io.OutputStream
      • com.esotericsoftware.kryo.io.Output
        • com.esotericsoftware.kryo.io.UnsafeOutput
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Closeable, java.io.Flushable, java.lang.AutoCloseable

    public final class UnsafeOutput
extends Output
    An optimized OutputStream that buffers data in a byte array and optionally flushes to another OutputStream. Utility methods are provided for efficiently writing primitive types, arrays of primitive types and strings. It uses @link{java.misc.Unsafe} to achieve a very good performance.

    Important notes:

  • This class increases performance, but may result in bigger size of serialized representation.
  • Bulk operations, e.g. on arrays of primitive types, are always using native byte order.
  • Fixed-size int, long, short, float and double elements are always written using native byte order.
  • Best performance is achieved if no variable length encoding for integers is used.
  • Output serialized using this class should always be deserilized using @link{UnsafeInput}

Author:
Roman Levenstein
